<task id="WKSP-003" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Define BFF API DTOs for workspace layout</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, types</tags>
    <estimated-effort>2h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>STANDARD</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>serial</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior TypeScript/C# developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Define C# record types for workspace layout API DTOs: WorkspaceLayoutDto, CreateWorkspaceLayoutRequest, UpdateWorkspaceLayoutRequest, SectionPlacementDto, and LayoutTemplateDto.</goal>
    <context>
      The BFF API (Sprk.Bff.Api) will expose CRUD endpoints for user workspace layouts stored in Dataverse.
      Before implementing endpoints (Phase 3), the DTO types must exist. These DTOs map to the Dataverse
      sprk_workspacelayout entity and the client-side TypeScript types.

      The API follows .NET 8 Minimal API patterns (ADR-001) with record types for immutable DTOs.
      Request types use data annotations for validation. Response types are clean projections of Dataverse data.

      Key data flow:
      - Dataverse stores: layout template ID, sections JSON (array of {sectionId, slotIndex}), sort order
      - API returns: full DTO with sections deserialized, template metadata resolved
      - Client sends: create/update requests with template ID, section placements, display name
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST use C# record types for all DTOs (immutable by convention)
      - MUST place files in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Workspace/ directory
      - MUST use System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations for request validation
      - MUST follow existing DTO naming conventions in the API project (check Models/ for patterns)
      - CreateWorkspaceLayoutRequest MUST validate: Name (required, max 100), LayoutTemplateId (required), Sections (required, non-empty)
      - WorkspaceLayoutDto MUST include: Id (Guid), Name, LayoutTemplateId, Sections (list), IsDefault, SortOrder, CreatedOn, ModifiedOn
      - SectionPlacementDto MUST include: SectionId (string), SlotIndex (int)
      - MUST NOT add any Dataverse/Graph SDK dependencies — these are pure DTOs
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-001-minimal-api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/</file>
    <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Examine existing DTO patterns in src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/ to match naming and structure conventions used by other feature areas.</step>
    <step id="2">Create the Models/Workspace/ directory and add SectionPlacementDto.cs as a record: SectionId (string), SlotIndex (int).</step>
    <step id="3">Create WorkspaceLayoutDto.cs as a record with: Id (Guid), Name (string), LayoutTemplateId (string), Sections (IReadOnlyList of SectionPlacementDto), IsDefault (bool), SortOrder (int), CreatedOn (DateTimeOffset), ModifiedOn (DateTimeOffset).</step>
    <step id="4">Create CreateWorkspaceLayoutRequest.cs with data annotation validation: [Required] Name ([MaxLength(100)]), [Required] LayoutTemplateId, [Required][MinLength(1)] Sections list.</step>
    <step id="5">Create UpdateWorkspaceLayoutRequest.cs with optional fields: Name, LayoutTemplateId, Sections, IsDefault, SortOrder. Use nullable types so partial updates are supported.</step>
    <step id="6">Create LayoutTemplateDto.cs as a lightweight record: Id (string), Name (string), Description (string), SlotCount (int) — for the GET /api/workspace/templates endpoint.</step>
    <step id="7">Verify the solution builds with dotnet build on the API project.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>All 5 DTO record types compile and are in the Sprk.Bff.Api.Models.Workspace namespace</criterion>
    <criterion>CreateWorkspaceLayoutRequest has [Required] on Name, LayoutTemplateId, and Sections with [MaxLength(100)] on Name</criterion>
    <criterion>WorkspaceLayoutDto includes all 8 properties: Id, Name, LayoutTemplateId, Sections, IsDefault, SortOrder, CreatedOn, ModifiedOn</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet build succeeds for the API project with no errors or warnings on the new files</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
